==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Block signal
<hw>Block signal</hw>. <fld>(Railroads)</fld> <def>One of the danger
signals or safety signals which guide the movement of trains in a block
system. The signal is often so coupled with a switch that act of opening
or closing the switch operates the signal also.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Block system</ent>⟦br⟧
